U.K. Stocks Advance After Bernanke Says Fed Prepared to Respond If Needed

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-07-13T14:17:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/u-k-stocks-advance-after-bernanke-says-fed-prepared-to-respond-if-needed.html
U.K. stocks gained as Federal
Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  said the central bank is
prepared to take additional action, including buying more bonds,
if the economy appears to be in danger of stalling.  The FTSE 100 Index climbed 0.4 percent to 5,891.92 at 3:15
p.m. in  London , having earlier lost 0.3 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  